name: Alpaca wool felt bead earrings
description: These gorgeous earrings would make a lovely unique gift for someone special! They have been handmade using brass ear wire and filigree balls. The felt beads have been individually made using hand-dyed alpaca wool and some other threads to add texture.

name: Barossa Valley Wildflowers Australiana postcard
description:
This is a photo I have taken of some local Barossa Valley wildflowers in the Barossa Goldfields, South Australia.

I have had the postcards professionally printed with a matte finish on the front and on the reverse side there is room for a message, address, stamp etc.

Postcard measures approx 10.4 X 13.8cm

This image is copyright so no scanning, reproducing or copying of this image please!.

name: Alpaca postcard
description:
Only a face a mother would love!!

This is a photo I have taken of one of my pet alpaca's named Kimba, he posed so beautifully and I think his expression is testament to the saying that 'beauty is in the eye of the beholder!!'. He had just been shawn so looks a little naked!!

I have had the postcards professionally printed and on the reverse side there is room for a message, address etc.

Kimba's image is copyright so no scanning, reproducing or copying of this image please!.

name: teddy bear artist postcard
description:
This postcard has been made from images I have taken of my handcrafted artist teddy bears. They have been professionally printed. The image copyright remains with me and may not be reproduced/scanned/copied without my permission.

The postcard will be sent inside an envelope unmarked and ready for use, it has a stamp space and writing space.
